<br>
I do #1 however, for a number of reasons...<br>
<br>
1&gt; Taunt isn't a 100% thing-press-a-button-succes. So waiting for the mob to turn away be4 pressing taunt only means I'm trusting my fate in the hands of the random generator gods. <br>
<br>
2&gt; If I press taunt all the time, i'll have more chances for the skill to work, hence my position on the hate list will be updated more, and therefore i'm less likely to loose aggro. In encounters where rogues are backstabbing, casters are nuking etc... do I have the luxury to watch a 700+ hitting mob turn around and try hitting the rogue ? I personally don't, hence my taunt mashing.<br>
<br>
It's probably all a matter of personal taste and playing style, but  this works for me.<br>
<br>
<br>
