<br>
To hold aggro I use disarm, kick, slam, and taunt. I TAUNT when the mob turns away from me. If after I push taunt and the mob turns to me it was a sucessful taunt. If it doesnt work I push it a second time and that usually does it. If it doesnt work after a second push then I say fook it and do Area Taunt. <br>
<br>
I've thought about this mashing I used to do and honestly reading this thread the sheer logistics of mashing a button over and over dont make sense. Why would verent make a class so dependent on repeatedly mashing a button? Wouldnt that create a boring and overly repetitive job? And I dont think verant would want us to be wearing out our mouse's by the insane clicking of taunt, unless of course they were selling Verant Brand mice. hehe. <br>
<br>
Smart taunt is god. Mashing is for amateurs. <br>
<br>
END of story!!!!!!!!!!<br>
