<br>
All I can say is that the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>RESULTS will PROVE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to anyone willing to try a change, not mashing, but actually only using taunt when mob turns, has made me a GOD of aggro management. I really couldn' believe the difference. In <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>FACT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">I LOOSE aggro MORE when I tried mashing again!</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> I believe every taunt usage actually resets the tables, as opposed to securing my position on the top, making it MORE likely I can be bumped from the top. Saving it for a mob's turn, actually requires very little usage. Additionally, I always make a hotkey for /shield on my slower, whether Shammy, or Chanter, and it is amazing how quick the mob will turn back on me if I loose aggro to slower...seems the Mobs <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>REALLY</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> hate sheilders! Plus that saves cleric mana, by keeping damage on me.<br>
<br>
