WAY too many button mashers!<br>
<br>
Frodlin,<br>
<br>
you remember that little bit I mentioned about skill and timing?<br>
<br>
This thread more than proves me right.<br>
<br>
There are some players (not just warriors mind you) who really need to do some reading.<br>
<br>
If you mash instead of choosing the time to hit the taunt button, then you are under-educated.<br>
<br>
Proximity does modify how much the mob hates you right now...yup.<br>
<br>
note that TAUNT has a maximum useful range as well....<br>
<br>
Mashing taunt means that you might not have it when the mob starts moving to beat on someone else.<br>
<br>
Timing +hate things (weapon swings, kick, anything that causes numerical hate) just after TAUNT is the #1 reason why some tanks hold aggro and why some cannot get a mob to even pay attention to them.<br>
<br>
Unless you can explain why 4 seconds is not enough for the mob to turn away from you and get alot closer to a caster (and make their hate thus more effective), you cannot win that point.<br>
<br>
The saddest point is that there IS such a thing as a proud button masher when they KNOW its not only less productive, but just plain deadly for the classes you are supposed to be protecting.<br>
<br>
Let me help,<br>
<br>
DO NOT MASH!<br>
Its comparative to a Cleric chain nuking instead of healing.  (nukes are fine here and there, but not being able to start a heal when you should have is deadly.)<br>
<br>
This is at least PART of why warriors complain of being terrible at aggro.<br>
<br>
